If you attach a player event listener and listen for `onTimelineChanged`, you can check the ad group count for the period becoming non-zero. Something like this:

```
Handler handler = new Handler(Looper.getMainLooper());
player.addListener(
    new Player.EventListener() {
      private boolean seenAdsLoader;

      @Override
      public void onTimelineChanged(Timeline timeline, int reason) {
        if (!seenAdsLoader
            && reason == Player.TIMELINE_CHANGE_REASON_SOURCE_UPDATE
            && timeline.getPeriod(/* periodIndex= */ 0, new Timeline.Period()).getAdGroupCount()
                > 0) {
          seenAdsLoader = true;
          handler.post(
              () -> Log.w("DEBUG", "Ads loader: " + imaAdsLoader.getAdsLoader()));
        }
      }
    });
```

Some notes/caveats:
- I think the posting to the main thread is not actually necessary in the current release but will be needed in future to ensure that the `AdsMediaSource` handles the timeline change event before the call to `getAdsLoader`, as the way this works in `ImaAdsLoader` is going to change soon.
- This snippet only works if the ad tag loaded is non-empty.
