this problem with video codec occurs after showing Admob interstitial ads if we close ads by tapping back button. **There is some problem with ExoPlayer reinitialization**. Before showing ad OnPause() and OnStop() are called. We destroy ExoPlayer. After showing ad we recreate ExoPlayer in the OnResume() method:
```
@Override
    public void onStart() {
        super.onStart();
        if (Util.SDK_INT > 23) {
            initExoPlayer();
        }
    }

    @Override
    protected void onPause() {
        super.onPause();
        if (Util.SDK_INT <= 23) {
            if (mFullScreen && !adWasShown) {
                setFullScreen();
            }
            simpleExoPlayerView.setVisibility(View.INVISIBLE);
            releaseExoPlayer();
        }
    }

    @Override
    protected void onResume() {
        super.onResume();
 if ((Util.SDK_INT <= 23 || exoPlayer == null)) {
            initExoPlayer();
        }
}
 @Override
    protected void onStop() {
        super.onStop();

        if (Util.SDK_INT > 23) {
            if (mFullScreen  && !adWasShown) {
                setFullScreen();
            }
            simpleExoPlayerView.setVisibility(View.INVISIBLE);
            releaseExoPlayer();
        }
}

 private void releaseExoPlayer() {
        if (exoPlayer != null) {
            exoPlayer.stop();
            exoPlayer.release();
            exoPlayer = null;
            trackSelector = null;
            dataSourceFactory = null;
            bandwidthMeter = null;
            mainHandler = null;
        }
    }

private void initExoPlayer() {

        if (exoPlayer == null) {
            mainHandler = new Handler();
            bandwidthMeter = new DefaultBandwidthMeter();

            dataSourceFactory = new DefaultDataSourceFactory(this, Util.getUserAgent(this, userAgent), bandwidthMeter);

            TrackSelection.Factory adaptiveTrackSelectionFactory = new AdaptiveTrackSelection.Factory(bandwidthMeter);
            trackSelector = new DefaultTrackSelector(adaptiveTrackSelectionFactory);

            exoPlayer = ExoPlayerFactory.newSimpleInstance(context, trackSelector);
            //exoPlayer.addListener(this);
            // 2.8.4
            exoPlayer.addListener(new PlayerEventListener());
            simpleExoPlayerView.setPlayer(exoPlayer);
        }
    }
```

I think the suggestion is to do something like:

```
  @Override
  public void onResume() {
    super.onResume();
    new Handler().post(this::initializePlayer);
  }
```

... instead of calling initializePlayer directly. The hypothesis is that somehow AdMob's cleanup tasks end up being queued on main thread after your `onResume` lifecycle method is queued. For the record, properly fixing the issue by having the ad player releasing synchronously on the main thread is tracked by [internal: b/127281295].

