This is not an issue, just some discussion about potential TsExtractor's race between HlsSampleSource and TsChunk.

When I read the code related to how HlsSampleSource read the chunk data, it's noticed that reading-data from DataSource and getting-sample from Extractor are in two threads:
- Reading data is in `TsChunk.load()`, which runs in a backgroud thread:

``` java
      while (bytesRead != -1 && !loadCanceled) {
        bytesRead = extractor.read(dataSource);
        if (bytesRead != -1) {
          loadPosition += bytesRead;
        }
      }
```
- Getting sample is in `HlsSampleSource.readData()`, which runs in ExoPlayer's event loop. And other functions access the extractor, e.g. 

``` java
    extractor.getSample(track, sampleHolder)
    extractor.discardUntil(i, timeUs);
```

I don't see any protection of the two threads accessing extractor;
Although there is `ConcurrentLinkedQueue` to protect the `SampleQueue.internalQueue` in TsExtractor, other members are not protected.

The question is, can we make sure there is no race accessing TsExtractor?
